  "script": "A pod of killer whales showed up just feet from a crowded beach, and swimmers had no idea. Orcas usually stay far offshore, but this pod came in close to hunt, slicing through the shallows after a school of fish while beachgoers watched from the sand. Killer whales are the ocean's top predator; they hunt in coordinated packs and have taken down sharks and even other whales. They're not known to attack people, but seeing a fin that tall that close is enough to clear the water fast. Lifeguards waved everyone in just in case. So why did they come in so close?",
